Nice work @camilleislasse  :slightly_smiling_face:

Some comments/ideas:

1. Not having support for non-fqcn services feels unintuitive  _(even though documented)_ – you may have e.g. `EnumSchemaProvider` which takes some identifier in constructor and then have one instance of the service per enum.
2. We should probably do a build-time check to ensure all the referenced schema provider services exist.
3. _(nice-to-have)_ Now a `SchemaProvider` has no context, which limits the use case a bit. We could have e.g.  `#[SchemaSource(provider: EntityEnumSchemaProvider::class, context: ['entity' => PaintColor::class])]` and pass `context` to `getSchemaFragment()`

